<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the configuration for video decoding.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAG_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>No configuration flags.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAG_HEIGHT_ALIGNMENT_MULTIPLE_32_REQUIRED">
    <summary>
      <para>The height of the output decoded surfaces must be a multiple of 32.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAG_POST_PROCESSING_SUPPORTED">
    <summary>
      <para>The driver supports post processing. If this flag is set, the host decoder can set up post-processing by using the conversion flags in the <see cref="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONVERSION_ARGUMENTS" />.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAG_REFERENCE_ONLY_ALLOCATIONS_REQUIRED">
    <summary>
      <para>Reference resources must be allocated with the <see cref="D3D12_RESOURCE_FLAG_VIDEO_DECODE_REFERENCE_ONLY" />  resource flag.  References textures must be separate from output textures, similar to performing a format conversion or downscale.  This flag must not be set for <see cref="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_TIER_3" /> or greater.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_CONFIGURATION_FLAG_ALLOW_RESOLUTION_CHANGE_ON_NON_KEY_FRAME">
    <summary>
      <para>The decode resolution can be changed on a non-key frame.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>